What's the difference?
Oh, my God.

9
00:00:39,172 --> 00:00:42,140
What, you don't wanna
buy burgers from a guy
who smells like pee?

10
00:00:42,142 --> 00:00:43,541
No one can place
where it's coming from.

11
00:00:43,543 --> 00:00:47,145
I can't believe
you'll close the restaurant
to go to a baseball game.

12
00:00:47,147 --> 00:00:50,581
Louise, this isn't just a game.
We bought an ad
at the ballpark.

13
00:00:50,583 --> 00:00:51,516
That's worth closing for, right?

14
00:00:51,518 --> 00:00:55,620
Oh, can't wait to see it.
It's gonna be so exciting.
We're famous.

15
00:00:55,622 --> 00:00:58,823
It looks like
a hot dog wrapper
stuck in the net.

16
00:00:58,825 --> 00:01:00,858
Like, a really
tiny hot dog.

17
00:01:00,860 --> 00:01:02,360
I did think it was gonna
be a little bigger.

18
00:01:02,362 --> 00:01:05,229
I think more people
would see your ad
if it was a urinal cake.

19
00:01:05,231 --> 00:01:07,865
Are you kidding?
I wish I could afford
a urinal cake ad.

20
00:01:07,867 --> 00:01:10,201
All this talk about cake
is making me hungry.

21
00:01:10,203 --> 00:01:14,338
I'm gonna flag down
the ice cream sandwich guy. Hey!

22
00:01:14,340 --> 00:01:15,273
Play ball!

23
00:01:15,275 --> 00:01:18,342
Welcome to opening day
of minor league baseball.

24
00:01:18,344 --> 00:01:21,746
Let's hear it for your
Wonder Wharf Wonderdogs!

25
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:25,516
[ Applause, Cheers ]
Please give a big
Wonderdog welcome to Phenom,

26
00:01:25,518 --> 00:01:27,718
the Korean bunt specialist!

27
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:30,721
I never realized baseball
had so much butt touching.

28
00:01:30,723 --> 00:01:32,690
That's how they
communicate, Tina.

29
00:01:32,692 --> 00:01:35,193
It's like braille,
but with butts.

30
00:01:35,195 --> 00:01:37,428
[ Gene ]
Read my butt!

31
00:01:37,729 --> 00:01:39,697
[ Groans ]
I'm bored.

32
00:01:39,699 --> 00:01:40,865
Boredom.
Boring sports.

33
00:01:40,867 --> 00:01:44,735
Hey, it's
the seventh-inning stretch.
Time for the mascot race.

34
00:01:44,737 --> 00:01:45,937
Well, hello!

35
00:01:45,939 --> 00:01:48,706
Please welcome the owner
of the Wonderdogs,

36
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:51,476
Mr. Calvin Fischoeder!

37
00:01:51,478 --> 00:01:52,176
Fish!

38
00:01:52,178 --> 00:01:53,344
It's that time.

39
00:01:53,346 --> 00:01:55,346
Now cheer for your
favorite mascot.

40
00:01:55,348 --> 00:01:56,781
Mr. Fischoeder
owns the team?

41
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:58,950
He owns the ballpark,
the team, Wonder Wharf.

42
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:01,886
I'm gonna marry
that man.
No, you're not.

43
00:02:01,888 --> 00:02:03,321
I wanna be rich!

44
00:02:03,323 --> 00:02:06,357
Don't be frightened.
I have a gun.

45
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:07,658
So get set.

46
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:09,460
- [ Gunshot ]
- [ Fans Cheer ]

47
00:02:09,462 --> 00:02:11,395
Where has this sport been
all my life?

48
00:02:11,397 --> 00:02:14,398
You know, I wear
the burger costume
all the time.

49
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,267
Maybe I could race
in one of these races, Dad.

50
00:02:16,269 --> 00:02:19,470
I bet it's impossible
to get in, Gene. I'm sure
you gotta know someone.

51
00:02:19,472 --> 00:02:22,006
You do.
It's Mr. Fischoeder,
our landlord.

52
00:02:22,008 --> 00:02:25,910
Well, I can't ask
a favor of a guy
I've never paid rent on time to.

53
00:02:25,912 --> 00:02:28,246
You're his son, Gene.
He'll ask him.

54
00:02:28,248 --> 00:02:28,846
Yay.
No, I won't.

55
00:02:28,848 --> 00:02:30,414
Now taking
the mound to pitch,

56
00:02:30,416 --> 00:02:33,284
former major league sensation,
Torpedo Jones.

57
00:02:33,286 --> 00:02:36,888
That can't be the same Torpe--
Kids, that's the
Torpedo Jones.

58
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:40,491
I can't believe
he's still playing.
God, he must be... my age.

59
00:02:40,493 --> 00:02:45,429
I speak for everyone here
when I say I don't know
what a Torpedo Jones is.

60
00:02:45,431 --> 00:02:46,564
Let me tell you, nobody--
We don't care.

61
00:02:46,566 --> 00:02:49,767
Gene, let me finish. Nobody--
That's what I was
trying to prevent.

62
00:02:49,769 --> 00:02:54,839
Nobody pitched like Torpedo.
I was there for his
greatest moment-- "The Pitch."

63
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:58,943
It was 15 years ago,
but I remember it
like it was 10.

64
00:02:58,945 --> 00:03:00,945
His pitch was
the split-finger skadootch.

65
00:03:00,947 --> 00:03:04,615
- [ Cheers ]
- Torpedo clinched the pennant
for us with that pitch.

66
00:03:04,617 --> 00:03:07,451
If he's so good,
why have we never
heard of this guy?

67
00:03:07,453 --> 00:03:09,353
Because he didn't
last long in the bigs.

68
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:11,589
The skadootch is just
one of those pitches.

69
00:03:11,591 --> 00:03:13,891
When it was on,
it was really on.

70
00:03:13,893 --> 00:03:15,426
But when it wasn't,

71
00:03:15,428 --> 00:03:19,897
it's like hitting candy
out of a baby's hand
with a bat.

72
00:03:19,899 --> 00:03:22,700
Wait. You mean it's hard
because babies hands
are so small?

73
00:03:22,702 --> 00:03:24,802
No, it's easy because--
How could you hit a baby?

74
00:03:24,804 --> 00:03:26,904
Nobody would hit
a baby's hand
with a bat in real life.

75
00:03:26,906 --> 00:03:28,940
I don't understand.
Was he fired
from the bigs...

76
00:03:28,942 --> 00:03:30,641
'cause he hit a baby
with a bat?

77
00:03:30,643 --> 00:03:33,211
I'm not interested
in talking to you.

78
00:03:33,845 --> 00:03:36,881
Sorry, Gene. I don't
see Fischoeder anywhere.
Let's get going.

79
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:40,952
That's all right.
I only wanted to do it
really, really bad.

80
00:03:40,954 --> 00:03:42,587
Oh, there's Torpedo!

81
00:03:42,589 --> 00:03:44,989
Dad, ask Torpedo
about the mascot races.

82
00:03:44,991 --> 00:03:46,424
Maybe he can
get Gene in.
Yeah!

83
00:03:46,426 --> 00:03:49,427
Kids, come on.
I can't bother Torpedo.
He's, like, my role model.

84
00:03:49,429 --> 00:03:52,930
Oh, that's creepy.
Your role model
is the same age as you?

85
00:03:52,932 --> 00:03:57,001
I would never have
another nine-year-old
as my role model.

86
00:03:57,003 --> 00:03:57,702
Hey, Torpedo!
Louise--

87
00:03:57,704 --> 00:04:02,473
My dad is a huge scout
for the Baseball League
of America.

88
00:04:02,475 --> 00:04:05,276
Kidding. But he has
a favor to ask you.

89
00:04:05,278 --> 00:04:08,479
[ Chuckles ]
Hi. I'm a huge fan.

90
00:04:08,481 --> 00:04:09,814
I was there
for "The Pitch."

91
00:04:09,816 --> 00:04:12,683
So, what can I do for ya?
Picture? Autograph?

92
00:04:12,685 --> 00:04:14,619
Three bucks each,
both for five.

93
00:04:14,621 --> 00:04:17,488
Uh, yeah,
both would be great.

94
00:04:17,490 --> 00:04:17,822
Dad!

95
00:04:17,824 --> 00:04:20,925
Oh. And, uh, my kid wants
to run in the mascot race.

96
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:22,693
You don't think--
Hey, Russell!

97
00:04:22,695 --> 00:04:25,496
Some kid here wants to run
in a mascot race.

98
00:04:25,498 --> 00:04:27,498
For you, Torpedo,
I'll make it happen.

99
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,667
I've gotta free up
one of these outfits.

100
00:04:29,669 --> 00:04:32,570
No, you don't.
I got my own.
It's a burger.

101
00:04:32,572 --> 00:04:34,338
Easy enough.
Thanks a lot, Torpedo.

102
00:04:34,340 --> 00:04:37,541
- Good luck out there, sport.
- Linda, did you hear that?

103
00:04:37,543 --> 00:04:38,576
Torpedo Jones
called me "sport."

104
00:04:38,578 --> 00:04:42,580
He didn't call you "sport."
He called Gene "sport."
No, he was looking right at me.

105
00:04:42,582 --> 00:04:45,850
Yeah. He called me "sport"
and he tousled my hair.

106
00:04:45,852 --> 00:04:47,952
It was great, Gene.
You were great.

107
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:49,587
I'm a great
tousle receiver.

108
00:04:49,589 --> 00:04:52,890
Wow. Wearing the burger suit
in the mascot race, Gene.

109
00:04:52,892 --> 00:04:54,925
That's advertising, huh?

110
00:04:54,927 --> 00:04:56,794
Don't touch me!

111
00:04:59,398 --> 00:05:04,101
It was so nice of Torpedo
to give us these seats
so we can watch Gene's race.

112
00:05:04,103 --> 00:05:07,004
You can really make out
the players' tattoos
from here.

113
00:05:07,006 --> 00:05:09,940
Makes you wonder
about the tattoos
we can't see.

114
00:05:09,942 --> 00:05:11,409
[ Quietly ]
On their butts.

115
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:14,078
How you doing, Gene?
You feeling fast?
No.

116
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:15,379
I feel queasy.

117
00:05:15,381 --> 00:05:16,947
Got some butterflies, ace?
Torpedo.

118
00:05:16,949 --> 00:05:19,850
Want my advice, kid?
It's a mascot race.

119
00:05:19,852 --> 00:05:21,919
All you gotta do
is stay on your feet.

120
00:05:21,921 --> 00:05:24,155
Let the other guys
trip over themselves.

121
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:27,558
It's time
for the mascot race!

122
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:29,093
Whoo-ee!
Goody.

123
00:05:29,095 --> 00:05:31,495
Remember,
you're an ambassador
for our restaurant.

124
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:34,665
So just try and run well,
'cause you don't run well.

125
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:36,033
Good luck
out there, sport.
Oh.

126
00:05:36,035 --> 00:05:38,202
Yeah, I thought earlier
you called me "sport," so--

127
00:05:38,204 --> 00:05:40,638
Nah, that was a nickname
for the kid there, Flash.

128
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:43,107
I'll take Flash.
Kids, call me Flash from now on.

129
00:05:43,109 --> 00:05:45,743
Let's split the diff
and call you Kiki.

130
00:05:45,745 --> 00:05:46,644
Kiki. I like it.

131
00:05:46,646 --> 00:05:50,448
Oh, Torpedo, here's
a little thank-you for
getting Gene in the race.

132
00:05:50,450 --> 00:05:52,483
I make burgers
for a living,

133
00:05:52,485 --> 00:05:54,418
so it's not weird
for me to give you this.

134
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:58,155
I don't think
it's weird at all, Bob.
Like a good burger.

135
00:05:58,157 --> 00:05:59,623
Mmm.
That's a good burger.

136
00:05:59,625 --> 00:06:01,659
Finish this guy
back on the mound.

137
00:06:01,661 --> 00:06:04,795
Ha! Torpedo Jones just said
I make a good burger.

138
00:06:04,797 --> 00:06:07,098
I want that on my tombstone.
Seriously, okay?

139
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:09,767
No, I already
got your tombstone
picked out for you.

140
00:06:09,769 --> 00:06:11,936
What? What is it?
It says, "Order up."

141
00:06:11,938 --> 00:06:13,838
[ Chuckles ]
That's good.
Let's go with that one.

142
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:18,042
Joining your
Wonder Wharf mascots today
is a special guest food--

143
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:21,479
a burger-- a boy
who is also a burger.

144
00:06:21,481 --> 00:06:23,447
And I have my gun.

145
00:06:23,449 --> 00:06:25,850
Ready! Set!

146
00:06:25,852 --> 00:06:27,618
[ Gunshot ]

147
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:28,519
Go get 'em, Gene!

148
00:06:28,521 --> 00:06:31,489
I reinforced the crotch
so he wouldn't tear it.

149
00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:34,024
Win, Gene!
Avenge Dad's death!

150
00:06:34,026 --> 00:06:36,927
[ Crowd ] Ohh!
[ Announcer ]
Down goes Sammy Sea Lion!

151
00:06:36,929 --> 00:06:39,563
- [ Imitating Explosions ]
- [ Groans ]

152
00:06:39,565 --> 00:06:41,665
Ooh! It's a two-mascot race.

153
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:43,534
Burger and Captain Pel I. Can.

154
00:06:43,536 --> 00:06:49,140
They're they go,
like two, fast, fiery-- Bew!

155
00:06:49,142 --> 00:06:50,007
[ Grunts ]

156
00:06:50,009 --> 00:06:52,943
The burger is your winner.
[ Imitates Trumpet Fanfare ]

157
00:06:52,945 --> 00:06:54,211
All right!

158
00:06:54,213 --> 00:06:55,846
Yeah, yeah, yeah!

159
00:06:55,848 --> 00:06:57,648
Well, congratulations,
young burger.

160
00:06:57,650 --> 00:06:59,917
Ladies and gentlemen,
you can purchase
delicious burgers...

161
00:06:59,919 --> 00:07:03,621
that look somewhat like him
right here at the park.

162
00:07:03,623 --> 00:07:05,556
And at my family's restaurant.

163
00:07:05,558 --> 00:07:08,659
And, uh, what's the name
of that restaurant?

164
00:07:08,661 --> 00:07:10,594
Ah-- It's-- It's--

165
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:12,930
God, I'm there every day.
Bob's Burgers!

166
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:14,832
It's-- Oh, my God.
Bob's Burgers!

167
00:07:14,834 --> 00:07:16,934
Gene! No!
Never mind. Never mind.
That's okay.

168
00:07:16,936 --> 00:07:19,737
Bob's Burgers! Oh, my God!
You can get everything
you expect from a burger...

169
00:07:19,739 --> 00:07:21,539
at whatever the name
of his restaurant is.

170
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:24,241
Bob's Burgers!
Oh, oh, I just remembered.
I just remembered.

171
00:07:24,243 --> 00:07:27,545
It's too late.
But you can get them
here at the park today.

172
00:07:27,547 --> 00:07:28,979
No! Say it!

173
00:07:28,981 --> 00:07:31,816
I won something!
I won! I won! I won something!

174
00:07:31,818 --> 00:07:34,018
Yeah, and you
didn't fall down
like everyone else.

175
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:35,719
- Tell that
to your grandkids.
- I will.

176
00:07:35,721 --> 00:07:40,691
Gene, are you kidding me?
The name of the restaurant
is Bob's Burgers!

177
00:07:40,693 --> 00:07:42,593
Well, I call you Dad.

178
00:07:42,595 --> 00:07:44,195
I think of it as Dad's Burgers.

179
00:07:44,197 --> 00:07:46,831
You live above it!
You work in it every day!

180
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:49,767
Bob, calm down.
Calm down. Calm down.
I'm sorry, Dad.

181
00:07:49,769 --> 00:07:52,536
Fine. He did great.
You did great, Gene.

182
00:07:52,538 --> 00:07:53,704
A gold medal!

183
00:07:53,706 --> 00:07:56,440
Oh, we should
get that bronzed.

184
00:07:56,741 --> 00:07:58,142
Strike three!
You're out!

185
00:07:58,144 --> 00:08:02,513
Torpedo's split-finger skadootch
has suddenly started clicking.

186
00:08:02,515 --> 00:08:04,048
I love that burger
of yours, Bob.

187
00:08:04,050 --> 00:08:08,619
Hey, after the game,
let's all go to Bob's Burgers.

188
00:08:08,621 --> 00:08:09,787
[ Fans Cheer ]
Whoo-hoo!

189
00:08:09,789 --> 00:08:13,858
Now that's
advertising, huh?

190
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:15,559
[ Cash Register Rings ]

191
00:08:15,561 --> 00:08:19,296
[ Crowd Chattering ]

192
00:08:19,298 --> 00:08:20,564
Ooh, Angel!

193
00:08:20,566 --> 00:08:22,967
Do they call you that
'cause you're such
a good boy?

194
00:08:22,969 --> 00:08:25,703
I did many bad things
to escape Cuba--
[ Gunfire ]

195
00:08:25,705 --> 00:08:28,839
[ Man Groans ]
things that haunt me
in the dark of the night.

196
00:08:28,841 --> 00:08:31,041
Aw!
How about another beer?

197
00:08:31,043 --> 00:08:33,744
Man, you kids got
a great dad, you know that?

198
00:08:33,746 --> 00:08:35,813
One wife, one family.
That's the way to do it.

199
00:08:35,815 --> 00:08:40,885
In the majors, most guys
got a whole bunch of families
spread out over the 50 states.

200
00:08:40,887 --> 00:08:42,920
When spring training starts,
you get your Florida wife.

201
00:08:42,922 --> 00:08:47,024
When it's regular season,
it's open season, if you
know what I'm talking about.

202
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:49,593
You kiss your home-field wife
and kids good-bye.

203
00:08:49,595 --> 00:08:50,961
You tell 'em
you'll miss 'em,
and you do.

204
00:08:50,963 --> 00:08:55,065
But you still take
some of their toys and
re-gift 'em for your away kids.

205
00:08:55,067 --> 00:08:57,067
I bet you're a great dad.

206
00:08:57,069 --> 00:08:58,135
And three great husbands.

207
00:08:58,137 --> 00:09:00,638
Mr. Torpedo,
I couldn't help but notice...

208
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:03,040
that the ball boy was
looking a little lethargic.

209
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:05,175
Yeah, he's got lupus
or rickets or something.

210
00:09:05,177 --> 00:09:08,178
I don't know why
we keep giving that job
to these sick kids.

211
00:09:08,180 --> 00:09:10,981
I was wondering if I
could offer my services.

212
00:09:10,983 --> 00:09:13,350
I'm very healthy.
[ Grunting ]

213
00:09:13,352 --> 00:09:15,686
Okay, okay, okay.
Whoa, whoa. Hey.

214
00:09:15,688 --> 00:09:17,688
You got the job.
Just stop doing that.

215
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:19,056
Here's your
first ball-girl duty.

216
00:09:19,058 --> 00:09:22,226
Bring me one
of your dad's burgers
before every game.

217
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:23,727
Okay.

218
00:09:24,029 --> 00:09:26,964
Here's the chewing tobacco
you wanted.
[ Grunts ]

219
00:09:26,966 --> 00:09:29,266
And your comic books.

220
00:09:29,268 --> 00:09:31,902
[ Spanish ]

221
00:09:36,241 --> 00:09:39,009
[ Scattered Cheers ]
Phenom, is it possible...

222
00:09:39,011 --> 00:09:42,046
to be in love
with 25 people at once?

223
00:09:42,048 --> 00:09:43,714
You're my favorite.

224
00:09:43,716 --> 00:09:46,650
Don't tell Angel.
He's fiery.

225
00:09:47,819 --> 00:09:49,954
- Strike three!
- [ Cheering ]

226
00:09:49,956 --> 00:09:52,890
Sound the alarm
because Torpedo is on fire.

227
00:09:52,892 --> 00:09:56,193
[ Imitates Fire Alarm ]
Fire! Fire! Fire!

228
00:09:56,195 --> 00:09:59,363
Not a good idea, Burt.
It's a crowded stadium.

229
00:09:59,365 --> 00:10:00,364
That Torpedo is amazing.

230
00:10:00,366 --> 00:10:03,867
Has he always been this good?
No, he hasn't been good
in a long time.

231
00:10:03,869 --> 00:10:06,003
He says my burgers
have helped him pitch better.

232
00:10:06,005 --> 00:10:08,005
How does a burger
help someone pitch better?

233
00:10:08,007 --> 00:10:10,341
Here you go, Bob--
a little souvenir.

234
00:10:10,343 --> 00:10:12,676
[ Chuckles ]
Thanks, buddy.

235
00:10:12,678 --> 00:10:15,245
Oh, slippery.
It's greasy, huh?

236
00:10:15,247 --> 00:10:17,314
[ Sniffs ]
What does this smell like?

237
00:10:17,316 --> 00:10:19,850
Hey, stop sniffing
Torpedo's balls.

238
00:10:19,852 --> 00:10:21,452
[ Laughs ]
Get it?

239
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:23,921
It's like you're
in love with him.

240
00:10:23,923 --> 00:10:25,255
Wait.
That's our burger.

241
00:10:25,257 --> 00:10:27,825
Oh, crap.
Torpedo's putting
my grease on the ball.

242
00:10:27,827 --> 00:10:30,260
That's how his skadootch
is skadootching so much.

243
00:10:30,262 --> 00:10:33,464
Your hero's using
your burger grease to win.
That's great.

244
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:39,269
No, Lin.
Torpedo is using
my burger grease to cheat.

245
00:10:39,271 --> 00:10:40,971
Oh.

246
00:10:43,108 --> 00:10:45,009
♪ [ Organ ]

247
00:10:45,011 --> 00:10:46,810
[ Crowd Clapping Rhythmically ]
So you helped
Torpedo cheat.

248
00:10:46,812 --> 00:10:49,313
If that means
the Wonderdogs keep coming
to the restaurant...

249
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:52,850
and bringing all sorts
of business with them,
I say big whoop.

250
00:10:52,852 --> 00:10:55,119
Let the old man
throw a greasy skadootch.

251
00:10:55,121 --> 00:10:58,255
[ Sighs ]
I don't even know
what to think about this.

252
00:10:58,257 --> 00:11:00,090
I-I gotta go take a leak.

253
00:11:00,092 --> 00:11:03,394
Oh, get me an ice cream
in a mini helmet!

254
00:11:04,062 --> 00:11:05,429
[ Urinating ]
[ Zipper Unzips ]

255
00:11:05,431 --> 00:11:06,797
Bob, you look glum.
[ Urinating ]

256
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:11,268
Oh, I, uh--
You don't hold your--
when you pee.

257
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:14,805
Why? It's not going anywhere.
Okay.

258
00:11:14,807 --> 00:11:16,273
Um, well,
what if you found out...

259
00:11:16,275 --> 00:11:18,509
that someone you knew
was doing something
sort of bad...

260
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:21,779
and you were helping them
do that sort of bad thing--

261
00:11:21,781 --> 00:11:23,280
Is it me?
Is it abortions?

262
00:11:23,282 --> 00:11:25,482
Wait. What?
Uh, what were you saying?

263
00:11:25,484 --> 00:11:27,785
Torpedo Jones
is greasing the ball,

264
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:29,687
and he's using
my grease to do it.

265
00:11:29,689 --> 00:11:33,857
Mm-mmm. Oh.
Come walk with me.

266
00:11:34,426 --> 00:11:35,926
Come behind the scenes.

267
00:11:35,928 --> 00:11:39,830
Torpedo's dazzling pitching
is putting more butts
in seats...

268
00:11:39,832 --> 00:11:40,998
than this stadium
can handle.

269
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:45,169
Is the roller coaster
gonna be okay without
those huge planks of wood?

270
00:11:45,171 --> 00:11:46,804
Sure, sure.
[ People Screaming Excitedly ]

271
00:11:46,806 --> 00:11:48,439
These people aren't paying
for extra wood, Bob.

272
00:11:48,441 --> 00:11:51,275
[ Roller Coaster Chugging ]
No one wants to ride
Extra Wood Mountain.

273
00:11:51,277 --> 00:11:54,945
Whoa! Watch out!
Extra nuts and bolts.
[ Nuts, Bolts Clanking ]

274
00:11:54,947 --> 00:11:55,479
Ow!

275
00:11:55,481 --> 00:11:56,814
People come
to baseball games...

276
00:11:56,816 --> 00:11:59,983
for the same reason
they come to
the amusement park--

277
00:11:59,985 --> 00:12:01,151
to be entertained!

278
00:12:01,153 --> 00:12:04,188
Does it really matter
if the games are rigged? No!

279
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:06,156
The games are rigged?
Yes!

280
00:12:06,158 --> 00:12:08,959
Oh. My wonderdog
is hanging out.

281
00:12:08,961 --> 00:12:10,060
Yes. Yes, it is.

282
00:12:10,062 --> 00:12:12,863
I got so caught up
in our conversation,
I forgot to zip.

283
00:12:12,865 --> 00:12:15,466
Yeah, I didn't want
to say anything.
Why not?

284
00:12:15,468 --> 00:12:16,967
I, uh--
Compliments are welcome.

285
00:12:16,969 --> 00:12:19,937
Where was I?
You were saying
the games are rigged.

286
00:12:19,939 --> 00:12:22,806
Yes. The games
are all rigged.

287
00:12:26,044 --> 00:12:28,545
I'm not letting my kids
play these games anymore.

288
00:12:28,547 --> 00:12:30,848
[ Fischoeder ]
But look
at these smiling faces.

289
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:32,516
Just like those
smiling faces--

290
00:12:32,518 --> 00:12:35,452
smiling at every skadootch
the Torpedo throws.

291
00:12:35,454 --> 00:12:39,456
They don't wanna know, Bob.
They don't wanna look
behind the curtain.

292
00:12:39,458 --> 00:12:44,261
I don't know. It just seems
like bad karma or something.

293
00:12:44,263 --> 00:12:44,828
Karma?

294
00:12:44,830 --> 00:12:47,297
There's no such thing
as karma.
[ Laughs ]

295
00:12:47,299 --> 00:12:49,500
Not in this town.
[ Roller Coaster Chugging ]

296
00:12:49,502 --> 00:12:51,068
[ Grunts ]
Oh, just kick 'em.

297
00:12:51,070 --> 00:12:54,004
- Kick 'em
right into the ocean.
- Okay.

298
00:12:54,006 --> 00:12:55,806
That's it.

299
00:12:56,007 --> 00:12:59,343
Wait. Why does Tornado
want our old grease
in a jar?

300
00:12:59,345 --> 00:13:01,145
It's Torpedo, Gene.
Oh.

301
00:13:01,147 --> 00:13:02,813
Uh, it helps him
pitch better.

302
00:13:02,815 --> 00:13:03,947
And don't forget.
It's a secret.

303
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:07,151
Why? Is it
against the rules?
Technically, yes.

304
00:13:07,153 --> 00:13:08,051
So then
it's cheating.

305
00:13:08,053 --> 00:13:11,922
No. What it is
is helping people
enjoy baseball more.

306
00:13:11,924 --> 00:13:12,856
It's entertainment.

307
00:13:12,858 --> 00:13:15,893
I'm confused.
Are you and Mom
getting divorced?

308
00:13:15,895 --> 00:13:17,427
What?
Oh, my God.
You are.

309
00:13:17,429 --> 00:13:18,228
I call Mom!
I call Dad!

310
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:21,532
You guys took both of them.
Enough.
Go fill the condiments.

311
00:13:21,534 --> 00:13:23,233
I call ketchup!
I call mustard!

312
00:13:23,235 --> 00:13:25,269
Aw.
You can do horseradish.

313
00:13:25,271 --> 00:13:26,303
There's not-- Okay.

314
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:29,173
Thanks, Bobby.
Hey, who wants a burger?

315
00:13:29,175 --> 00:13:32,009
On the Torpedo.
Hooray!

316
00:13:32,177 --> 00:13:35,112
Gene, you're
defending your title.
Are you nervous?

317
00:13:35,114 --> 00:13:36,380
Why don't you ask
my diarrhea?

318
00:13:36,382 --> 00:13:40,517
You should be nervous.
You're a chubby kid
in a mascot suit.

319
00:13:40,519 --> 00:13:42,820
That's what I'm saying.
I should cheat.

320
00:13:42,822 --> 00:13:45,556
Dad says it's okay
when it's for entertainment.

321
00:13:45,558 --> 00:13:46,990
That's right. Let's cheat.

322
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:48,292
- You see that pelican?
- [ Gene ]
Yeah.

323
00:13:48,294 --> 00:13:52,496
You're running, right?
You have a switchblade
taped to your shoe.

324
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:53,297
- He does?
- He will.

325
00:13:53,299 --> 00:13:55,632
And on your other shoe,
you'll have a lemon.

326
00:13:55,634 --> 00:13:58,902
Stab, stab, stab!
Sting, sting, sting!

327
00:13:58,904 --> 00:13:59,903
"What are you doing?"

328
00:13:59,905 --> 00:14:02,873
"I'm squeezing lemon
into your wound."

329
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:04,041
Sweet baby blade foot.

330
00:14:04,043 --> 00:14:07,077
Or... I can give him
a nudge and tip him over.

331
00:14:07,079 --> 00:14:09,313
[ Groans ]
Really?
Yeah. He's top-heavy.

332
00:14:09,315 --> 00:14:11,381
I'll just give him
a little tippity-tap.

333
00:14:11,383 --> 00:14:14,551
Well, I'm still gluing
a knife to my foot.

334
00:14:14,553 --> 00:14:16,186
[ Gunshot ]

335
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:18,121
Yay, Gene! Go, Gene!
That-a-way, Son.

336
00:14:18,123 --> 00:14:20,624
- [ Panting ]
- [ Fans Cheering ]

337
00:14:20,626 --> 00:14:22,059
Tippity-tap.
[ Grunts ]

338
00:14:22,061 --> 00:14:26,096
[ Phil ]
Ooh! it's
a three-mascot pile-up.

339
00:14:26,098 --> 00:14:27,497
Go, Gene! All right! Go!

340
00:14:27,499 --> 00:14:31,501
[ Burt ]
The Boy Burger wins again!
How about that?

341
00:14:31,503 --> 00:14:35,606
Hey, how about this, Phil?
[ Imitates Whooping Siren ]

342
00:14:35,608 --> 00:14:38,542
I don't know, Burt.
I'm not so sure about that.

343
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:39,343
Yay!

344
00:14:39,345 --> 00:14:40,577
I won! I won again!

345
00:14:40,579 --> 00:14:44,281
My brother won.
Guys, take off
your shirts.

346
00:14:44,283 --> 00:14:46,083
[ Grunting ]

347
00:14:46,085 --> 00:14:49,319
- Good arm pumping, baby.
- That's how I disguised
the push.

348
00:14:49,321 --> 00:14:52,689
- What push?
- He pushed the Cotton Candy
mascot so he'd fall over.

349
00:14:52,691 --> 00:14:56,059
- Hooray for cheating.
- Gene, how could you?
You know that's wrong.

350
00:14:56,061 --> 00:14:59,663
Uh-uh-uh.
Not when it's entertainment.
You said it yourself.

351
00:14:59,665 --> 00:15:03,533
You told them
cheating is okay?
No, I didn't, Linda.

352
00:15:03,535 --> 00:15:05,068
Yes, he did.

353
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,536
Oh, Bobby.
Oh, crap.

354
00:15:06,538 --> 00:15:10,607
Go get me
a soft serve.
And make it a swirl!

355
00:15:14,612 --> 00:15:17,981
Look, Gene,
when I said it's okay to cheat,
I meant for Torpedo,

356
00:15:17,983 --> 00:15:19,950
not for you to cheat
in your mascot race.

357
00:15:19,952 --> 00:15:22,352
You should
really give back
one of those medals.

358
00:15:22,354 --> 00:15:25,155
Ooh, but I wanna get a picture
of you wearing them
before you do.

359
00:15:25,157 --> 00:15:27,024
I'm not giving back
my medal!

360
00:15:27,026 --> 00:15:28,425
Those suckers got
their money's worth, Pops.

361
00:15:28,427 --> 00:15:32,095
I'm good for business, Dad.
From now on,
there'll be no more cheating.

362
00:15:32,097 --> 00:15:35,966
- Does that mean I shouldn't
give Torpedo this grease?
- That's right, Tina.

363
00:15:35,968 --> 00:15:39,369
Yes. No more cheating
for anyone
in this house.

364
00:15:39,371 --> 00:15:42,606
From now on, I won't wear
my tummy-tuck jeans.

365
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:46,543
And good-bye, Brazilian.
Hello, rain forest.

366
00:15:47,645 --> 00:15:48,545
Sorry, Dad.

367
00:15:48,547 --> 00:15:49,513
But if I win tomorrow,

368
00:15:49,515 --> 00:15:53,383
I'll be the first mascot ever
to win three races in a row.

369
00:15:53,385 --> 00:15:56,119
- I'm a top.
- You mean you're on top.

370
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:59,456
No. I'm a top.
[ Grunts ]

371
00:16:00,091 --> 00:16:01,191
[ Fans Cheering ]

372
00:16:01,193 --> 00:16:02,592
Shew. I was
starting to think...

373
00:16:02,594 --> 00:16:04,561
maybe you were
gonna leave me
high and dry here.

374
00:16:04,563 --> 00:16:07,164
Well, what's in this jar
is worth the wait.

375
00:16:07,166 --> 00:16:09,499
What the--
"You don't need to cheat.

376
00:16:09,501 --> 00:16:10,801
You can win without me.

377
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:14,571
If you try your hardest,
you've already won.
Love, Bob's grease."

378
00:16:14,573 --> 00:16:17,574
That's right, Torpedo.
You can win without my grease.

379
00:16:17,576 --> 00:16:19,242
It just took me
believing in you.

380
00:16:19,244 --> 00:16:22,212
Now, listen.
Gene's about to race,
and since you're his role model,

381
00:16:22,214 --> 00:16:26,216
I'm hoping you'll tell Gene
he can win without cheating,
just like you.

382
00:16:26,218 --> 00:16:28,552
- Who the hell's Gene?
- That's... my son.

383
00:16:28,554 --> 00:16:31,221
You're his role model,
and you're my role model too.

384
00:16:31,223 --> 00:16:35,025
Wh-- I can't be
your role model.
We're the same age.

385
00:16:35,027 --> 00:16:37,260
What's this mean?
You cutting me off, Bob-O?

386
00:16:37,262 --> 00:16:39,296
Torpedo, I'm cutting you free.

387
00:16:39,298 --> 00:16:40,664
Come here.
Wait. What are you gonna do?

388
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:42,599
I'm gonna hug you.
Slow down there, tiger.

389
00:16:42,601 --> 00:16:45,302
Guess I'll have to make
this grease last
the whole season.

390
00:16:45,304 --> 00:16:49,072
I should have never
given you my grease.
I created a monster.

391
00:16:49,074 --> 00:16:50,774
You think you
started my greasing?

392
00:16:50,776 --> 00:16:53,410
I've always cheated, Bobby.

393
00:16:53,412 --> 00:16:55,045
Not "The Pitch."

394
00:16:55,047 --> 00:16:55,712
Oh, definitely "The Pitch."

395
00:16:55,714 --> 00:17:00,250
That game, I had a pat
of butter in my right nostril,
sex jelly in my armpit.

396
00:17:00,252 --> 00:17:04,621
Hell, I was on prescription
drugs to stimulate
production of earwax.

397
00:17:04,623 --> 00:17:06,323
And "The Pitch"?
That was courtesy...

398
00:17:06,325 --> 00:17:10,060
of some
black-market whale blubber
I bought off some Eskimos.

399
00:17:10,062 --> 00:17:12,329
Cute note though, Bob.
Bit of advice:

400
00:17:12,331 --> 00:17:14,831
If you want a role model,
pick an old guy.

401
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:18,035
By the time you grow up,
they're dead.

402
00:17:18,669 --> 00:17:20,270
[ Sighs ]
Didn't go great. Gene!

403
00:17:20,272 --> 00:17:23,373
I'm sure it was fine.
Torpedo seems like
a reasonable guy.

404
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:26,543
Torpedo Jones wants you
out of his seats this second.

405
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:29,079
What a schmuck.
Gene!

406
00:17:29,514 --> 00:17:32,149
[ Phil ] It's
the seventh-inning stretch.

407
00:17:32,151 --> 00:17:33,150
Mascots are lining up.

408
00:17:33,152 --> 00:17:34,418
All right,
maybe I have an idea.

409
00:17:34,420 --> 00:17:39,723
Hi, fellas. I'd love to say
a few words to my son,
the burger, over the P.A.

410
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:41,391
Excuse me.
Uh, okay.

411
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:42,559
[ Chuckles ]
Highly unusual.

412
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:45,128
Doesn't matter.
None of this matters.

413
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:47,264
Gene. Up here.

414
00:17:47,266 --> 00:17:47,664
Jesus?

415
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:50,700
No, Gene, it's your father.
I'm up here.

416
00:17:50,702 --> 00:17:51,668
You're dead?

417
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:53,270
[ Chuckles ]
Yes.
[ Gasps ]

418
00:17:53,272 --> 00:17:55,372
No, I'm-I'm--
[ Chuckles ] I'm kidding.

419
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:58,275
I'm up here in the booth.
Right here. See me?

420
00:17:58,277 --> 00:18:00,577
[ Sniffs ]
Boy, this microphone
smells like beer.

421
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:03,346
Well, let's just say A.A.
was "A" waste of time.

422
00:18:03,348 --> 00:18:07,584
Winning isn't everything, Gene.
Yes, we're all here
to be entertained.

423
00:18:07,586 --> 00:18:09,419
But if you, um,
cut corners now,

424
00:18:09,421 --> 00:18:13,690
the next thing you know
you'll be hiding lard
in your nose...

425
00:18:13,692 --> 00:18:16,193
or taking wood
out of roller coasters.

426
00:18:16,195 --> 00:18:18,829
Hey, hey, all right,
that's enough of that.

427
00:18:18,831 --> 00:18:20,263
Let's start the race.

428
00:18:20,265 --> 00:18:23,700
I'm trying to talk to my son.
Gene, run clean.

429
00:18:23,702 --> 00:18:24,534
On your mark!

430
00:18:24,536 --> 00:18:26,636
- Gene, what are
you gonna do?
- I don't know.

431
00:18:26,638 --> 00:18:29,306
You're gonna cheat.
That's what you're gonna do.

432
00:18:29,308 --> 00:18:31,308
You're gonna win
by cheating!

433
00:18:31,310 --> 00:18:33,677
♪ [ Organ: "Call to the Post" ]

434
00:18:33,679 --> 00:18:35,145
[ Gunshot ]

435
00:18:35,147 --> 00:18:36,113
[ Panting ]

436
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:39,716
Who wants to see the burger
win three in a row?
[ Cheering ]

437
00:18:39,718 --> 00:18:41,885
Gene, listen to me.
You know what to do.

438
00:18:41,887 --> 00:18:44,387
Bob, triple crown for burger.

439
00:18:44,389 --> 00:18:47,157
- Good for your business.
- See?

440
00:18:47,159 --> 00:18:50,227
No, Gene. Don't worry
about the advertising.

441
00:18:50,229 --> 00:18:51,728
What are you doing?
It's a starter's pistol.

442
00:18:51,730 --> 00:18:54,731
- It's a real gun. Get down.
- [ Gunshot ]
- What?

443
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:56,500
Stop shooting.
This is crazy.

444
00:18:56,502 --> 00:18:57,767
[ Gunshots Stop ]
Oh, good. He stopped.

445
00:18:57,769 --> 00:19:01,271
He's just out of bullets.
And down goes Cotton Candy.

446
00:19:01,273 --> 00:19:02,672
It's a two-mascot race.

447
00:19:02,674 --> 00:19:04,274
Gene, do the right thing.

448
00:19:04,276 --> 00:19:08,345
Yeah! You can win
on your own, Gene! Probably.

449
00:19:08,347 --> 00:19:08,912
[ Pants ]

450
00:19:08,914 --> 00:19:12,549
[ In Slow-motion ]
Hey.

451
00:19:13,951 --> 00:19:16,186
All right. Fine.

452
00:19:16,188 --> 00:19:16,786
[ Groans ]

453
00:19:16,788 --> 00:19:20,190
Whoa, whoa!
Don't push him!
He was gonna push you!

454
00:19:20,192 --> 00:19:23,527
[ Burt ]
Congratulations
to Captain Pel I. Can.

455
00:19:23,529 --> 00:19:24,895
Oh, Gene, sorry, buddy.

456
00:19:24,897 --> 00:19:27,397
Looks like karma
caught up to you.

457
00:19:27,399 --> 00:19:30,233
Bob, I told you
there's no such thing as karma.

458
00:19:30,235 --> 00:19:33,203
- Uh, yes, there is.
- No, I'm afraid there isn't.

459
00:19:33,205 --> 00:19:34,871
I'm afraid there is.

460
00:19:34,873 --> 00:19:36,640
Is not.

461
00:19:37,775 --> 00:19:41,811
[ Fans Gasping, Chattering ]

462
00:19:43,281 --> 00:19:44,881
[ Wheels Screech ]

463
00:19:46,284 --> 00:19:48,818
[ Metal Clanging, Stops ]

464
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:51,388
Oh, crap.

465
00:19:51,522 --> 00:19:54,724
See, Gene,
this is what happens
when you cheat.

466
00:19:54,726 --> 00:19:55,959
That was incredible.

467
00:19:55,961 --> 00:19:59,462
Cheating is amazing!
[ Groans ]

468
00:19:59,464 --> 00:20:00,363
Bob?

469
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:01,598
Oh. Uh, hi.

470
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:03,667
Sorry about
your roller coaster.

471
00:20:03,669 --> 00:20:05,902
Ah, roller coasters
come and go,

472
00:20:05,904 --> 00:20:09,306
but Bobs are
once in a lifetime.

473
00:20:09,308 --> 00:20:10,340
I admire you.
You do?

474
00:20:10,342 --> 00:20:14,578
You remind me of my father.
He was honest,
and he worked hard.

475
00:20:14,580 --> 00:20:17,480
You an immigrant, Bob?
Um, no.

476
00:20:17,482 --> 00:20:18,748
Just swarthy?
I guess.

477
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:21,551
What's swarthy?
Um, dark and hairy.

478
00:20:21,553 --> 00:20:23,720
That's you.
And me in the future.

479
00:20:23,722 --> 00:20:25,989
Well, unlike you,
my father made
a fortune.

480
00:20:25,991 --> 00:20:28,925
But in many other ways,
you guys are the same--

481
00:20:28,927 --> 00:20:31,761
two decent,
swarthy peas in a pod.

482
00:20:31,763 --> 00:20:36,600
One rich and one...
just scraping by.
Thanks.

483
00:20:36,602 --> 00:20:38,868
Well, we're off
to get a massage.

484
00:20:38,870 --> 00:20:40,904
Come on, Wonderdog.
Down, boy.

485
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:44,007
He's gone, Dad.
My future husband's gone.

486
00:20:44,009 --> 00:20:45,642
You drove him away!

487
00:20:45,644 --> 00:20:46,443
Tina, what you
got there?

488
00:20:46,445 --> 00:20:50,347
The team signed a ball
so I'd have something
to remember them by.

489
00:20:50,349 --> 00:20:51,581
And I took
this jockstrap.

490
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:55,485
Okay, sweetie.
[ Chuckles ]
Let's throw that in the wash.

491
00:20:55,487 --> 00:20:56,853
No. Mm-mmm.
Come on. Give it to me.

492
00:20:56,855 --> 00:21:00,757
Do you know
how many venereal diseases
those baseball players have?

493
00:21:00,759 --> 00:21:02,592
I don't care.
Whose was it?

494
00:21:02,594 --> 00:21:04,694
Smells like Angel.
Angel.

495
00:21:04,696 --> 00:21:06,663
[ Tina ]
But don't tell Phenom.

496
00:21:06,665 --> 00:21:08,064
♪ [ Organ ]
[ Fischoeder ]
Ladies and gentlemen,

497
00:21:08,066 --> 00:21:11,868
you can purchase
delicious burgers
that look somewhat like him...

498
00:21:11,870 --> 00:21:13,303
right here at the park.

499
00:21:13,305 --> 00:21:15,305
[ Gene ]
And at my family's restaurant.

500
00:21:15,307 --> 00:21:18,341
[ Fischoeder ]
And, uh, what's the name
of that restaurant?

501
00:21:18,343 --> 00:21:20,043
[ Gene ]
Ah-- It's-- It's--

502
00:21:20,045 --> 00:21:22,912
God, I'm there every day.
[ Bob ]
Bob's Burgers!

503
00:21:22,914 --> 00:21:24,080
[ Gene ]
It's-- Oh, my God.

504
00:21:24,082 --> 00:21:25,382
[ Bob ] Bob's Burgers!

505
00:21:25,384 --> 00:21:25,815
Gene! No!

506
00:21:25,817 --> 00:21:27,584
[ Fischoeder ]
Never mind. That's okay.
[ Bob ] Bob's Burgers!

507
00:21:27,586 --> 00:21:29,552
[ Fischoeder ]
You can get everything
you expect from a burger...

508
00:21:29,554 --> 00:21:32,389
at whatever
the name
of his restaurant is.

509
00:21:32,391 --> 00:21:33,056
[ Bob ]
Bob's Burgers!

510
00:21:33,058 --> 00:21:34,758
[ Gene ]
I just remembered.
I just remembered.

511
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:37,794
[ Fischoeder ]
It's too late.
[ Bob ] No! Say it!

